Second, I have a few thoughts on the topic of reserving. I am in the same situation of your friend. For the last few months I have been a sliver into 53, joining every Vox raid I can for that elusive scale.<br>
<br>
Personally I hate reserving - or things being reserved. We all join these raids because of the nice - and for some necessary - items that drops. The xp arent that good anyhow :o )<br>
<br>
One of the problem of reserving is that other characters of that class might not show up. As for Vox, I think both paladins and bards are good to have, for their stuns and resists respectively. However since 60 warriors of level 45 probably still can take her down, its much the call of the raid leader.<br>
<br>
