<br>
One thing is certain, if an item is being reserved then it should be in the original post in capital letters. More than once have I shown up, done my part and only found out that a scale or book was reserved when we camped to chat..<br>
<br>
You also wrote that its preferable to give the epic loots to high level characters. In one way I tend to agree with this, since these have fewer levels to rejoin Vox/Naggy raids and gain those crucial parts of their epics. On the other hand its no fun spending a few hours, and then not even get a chance to twitch your bloodied fingers in anticipation.<br>
<br>
I have two suggestions as what to do about this. One is simply to give the higher level characters a bigger chance on the roll. Anyone from level 46-50 get one chance, a level 51 gets 2 and so on. Thus your level 53 friend would get four chances as opposed to newbie paladins 1... He could still loose though.<br>
<br>
The other suggestion is that the person for whom something is reserved bring something of his own that can be randomed out in return - like the bag normally goes to a monk in return for tinkerings. This way the other players could still come out richer - even if what you are looking for is strictly reserved. I know that I for one would give up on some of my good equipment to finally get that scale and be able to level on.<br>
<br>
All that being said, its your call Quichan. You are the raid leader and the rest of us have the option not to attend if we dont like the rules.<br>
<br>
I am looking forward to another test of strength with the Lady. May it be as swift and painless as in your dreams :o )<br>
<br>
